      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 48 九三</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>九三：井渫不食，為我民惻，可用汲，王明，并受其福。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The third NINE, undivided, shows a well, which has been cleared out, but is not used. Our hearts are sorry for this, for the water might be drawn out and used. If the king were (only) intelligent, both he and we might receive the benefit of it.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
